<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Next is our healing line whilst compared to clerics, druids and shamans. Where once we were a decent asset as back-up healers most of the healing classes got an increase pre-pop in order to prepare them for the coming encounters. This left paladins wondering where exactly our role will turn once the new expansion goes live.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Healing wave of prexus and celestial cleansing are great heals, and with the new group heal in PoP and single target heals of Remedy and Divine light we will still be decent back up healers/ae healers, no complaints by me in this department.<br>
<br>
However, i do agree with you about the stun thing, with the increase in level limit i believe stun should be able to work on mobs up to 60 now, and divine stun(AA) on mobs up to 65. but, can only wait and see on that.<br>
<br>
and, as for the brells upgrade compared to the beastlord spell, do they stack? if so then no problems there..<br>
<br>
as far as lay hands, im thinking it wasnt supposed to heal as much as it was. it was healing 2801 or something at lvl 60, not quite sure, i dont usually pay attention to it. but a 300 point nerf isnt a big deal, it was that much less before the 10percent healing penalty was removed(around 2500 i think), so maybe they fixed it now, by accidently giving it extra before. regardless point is, Lay Hands is not a heal, its a save your ass till the real heal spell lands imo.<br>
<br>
I think Paladins are perfectly fine in my opinion, i have been astounded by all the complaining and bitching on the paladin boards, usually there isnt much complaining at all. the only thing that is gonna hurt a paladin i think is the upgrade to healing wave of prexus, its 850mana for 900hp.. i noticed i fizzel hwop a decent amount of the time, that is 650 mana spell. that 850mana spell fizzled isnt going to be fun either because hybrids cant specialize to reduce mana cost and fizzle rate. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=15391">Tormarc Truelight</a><BR>
